                raise ValidationError('Contains invalid value %s' % item)
```

@dhalperi I didn't write the Java bindings so I can't give you a definitive answer.

For the new CMake build system using a static libz3 and building python/.NET/Java bindings is actually forbidden (the configure step will fail) because the way they are currently implemented requires a dynamic library. I know for certain that the Python bindings requiring a dynamic library because they use `ctypes.CDLL()` to load the library.

For the Java bindings the generated `Native.java` contains this code

```java
  static {
    try { System.loadLibrary("z3java"); }
    catch (UnsatisfiedLinkError ex) { System.loadLibrary("libz3java"); }
  }
```

`libz3java.so` is a small native code library (built from the generated `Native.cpp` file) that itself links to `libz3.so`. I don't know if Java can load a static library at runtime. My suspicion would be no but I don't have much expertise with Java so I could be wrong.

